---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ThemeToggle from "../components/ThemeToggle.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy â€” Luno" description="Luno's privacy policy. Your notes stay on your device.">
  <ThemeToggle />
  <main class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <article class="prose mx-auto max-w-3xl" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg" style="color: var(--color-text-1);">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">Your Data Stays Yours</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-1);">
        Luno is designed with privacy at its core. Your notes are stored on your device and are never
        sent to external servers for processing. On-device AI handles categorization locally.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">What We Collect</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-1);">
        If you join the waitlist, we collect only your email address via Formspree. We do not track
        your usage, collect analytics, or store any personal data beyond what you voluntarily provide.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">iCloud Sync</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-1);">
        If you enable iCloud sync, your notes are synced through Apple's CloudKit infrastructure,
        encrypted in transit and at rest. Luno does not have access to your iCloud data.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-0);">Contact</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-1);">
        Questions about privacy? Reach out via our GitHub repository.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
